Solanum ratale

is endemic to Fiji on the islands of Viti Levu and Vanua Levu. It is known from elevation of 200 to 800 m but may grow at lower elevation near Suva (but see below). The habitat has been recorded as logged-off forest (
Degener 14324
) or dense forest along streams (
Smith 5370
).
